The paper also discusses problems related to graphs and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the clique problem, which is a classic problem in computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the framework of Bodlaender et al. and Fortnow and Santhanam, which are related to logic and automata theory, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible sub-category as well.
